    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-19T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="753"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5068: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-20T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 20, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 20—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following telegram has been sent to American Consul at Geneva: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 20, 11 a.m. For the Secretary. Your April 18, 11 p.m.<note n="74"
                                xml:id="d753fn74">See telegram No. 82, April 18, midnight, from the
                                Minister in Switzerland, <ref target="#pg_697">p. 697</ref>.</note>
                            I concur in colleagues’ views as set forth in Shanghai’s April 19, 3
                            p.m., to Geneva.”<note n="75" xml:id="d753fn75">See telegram No. 88,
                                April 23, 2 p.m., from the Minister in Switzerland, <ref
                                    target="#pg_721">p. 721</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
